<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Hehe... go to <a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_pottery.htm" title="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_pottery.htm" target="akztarg">http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/re...pottery.htm</a> and you have an excellent source on how to do pottery from 0 to 250.  Recipes are in order of trivial.  Basically to do pottery, you go to a pottery wheel and combine clay, water, and a sketch, then take the unfired item, place it in the kiln with a firing sheet (and sometimes glaze) to make the fired item.  Firing in the kiln always trics a lot lower than the pottery wheel, so unless you actually need the item or the item has a reasonable sale value, just destroy the unfired item if you're doing pottery just for skill.  Start out my making tons and tons of small bowls until they triv.</p>
